  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Social Cohesion through Reintegration, Revitalisation and Stabilisation Assistance in Iraq</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project focuses on conflict resolution, strengthening social cohesion between communities and enhancing the resilience of people affected by conflict and displacement to promote long term and sustainable peace in Iraq&#x2019;s post-crisis context. In particular, the project aims to strengthen capacity of individuals and communities to mitigate tensions, peacefully resolve and manage conflict and channel stress and frustration effectively. Programming includes the establishment and running of IOM&#x2019;s so-called pop-up community centres placed in areas that are affected by local conflict and tensions due to displacement by either absorbing a large amount of internally displaced persons or returnees. In these centres, IOM creates opportunities for diverse groups to come together, provide mental health and psychosocial support, provide rehabilitation of key social and economic community infrastructure and provide for strengthening of community structures and local governance through capacity building.</narrative>
  </description>
